# Reflection — Assignment 7

## Challenges Faced

One of the main challenges in this assignment was selecting the most appropriate GitHub template. While several templates are available, choosing one that aligns with Agile principles and supports efficient workflow required careful evaluation.

Another challenge was customizing the Kanban board. Deciding which additional columns to include, such as "Testing" and "Blocked", required understanding how real development workflows operate.

Linking issues from previous assignments and organizing them into the board was also challenging. It required ensuring consistency between user stories, sprint tasks, and Kanban items.

Comparing GitHub Projects with other tools such as Trello and Jira was also insightful. GitHub integrates directly with code and issues, making it efficient for developers, while tools like Jira offer more advanced project management features.

## Lessons Learned

This assignment improved my understanding of Agile workflow management using Kanban boards. It demonstrated how tasks can be visualized and managed effectively.

I also learned the importance of automation in project management. Automated Kanban reduces manual work and improves efficiency.

Additionally, I gained experience in using GitHub Projects as a real-world Agile tool.

## Conclusion

Overall, this assignment provided valuable experience in project management and Agile practices. It showed how to organize, track, and manage development tasks effectively using a Kanban board.